Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm chips (peeling optional).

Pop the chips onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Toss with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Halve, peel and finely chop the @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped).

Roughly chop the @coriander{5%g} (stalks and all).

Peel and grate the @garlic{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Cut the @tomato{2} into 2cm chunks. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Trim half the @cucumber{1/2} (double for 4p). Quarter lengthways then chop widthways into small pieces.

Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%pack} in a #sieve{}.

Add the drained chickpeas to a large #bowl{} and mash to a paste with a #fork{}.

Mix the onion, garlic, @ground cumin{2%sachet}, and coriander into the chickpeas.

Sprinkle over @flour{2%tbsp} (double for 4p).

Season with @salt{1%tsp} and @pepper{1/2%tsp} (double both for 4p). Mix well to combine.

> TIP: You can also use a potato masher to crush the chickpeas if you prefer.

Using your hands, form small round balls from the falafel mixture (4 per person).

Press the balls tightly together, flattening to make mini patty shapes.

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a good glug of @oil{to taste}.

When the oil is hot, fry the falafels until golden brown all over, ~{3-4%mins} on each side.

Once cooked, transfer to a plate lined with #kitchen paper{} to drain any excess oil.

Meanwhile, mix the @yoghurt{150%g} with the chopped cucumber and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. 
Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Pop the @flatbread{2} into the oven to warm, ~{1-2%mins}.

Just before serving, toss the @salad leaves{40%g} with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Allow everyone to top their own warm flatbreads with tzatziki, tomato, rocket salad and golden falafels.

Serve the chips on the side.